In December 2010, Anderson was named by ''[[We Love Soaps]]'' as one of the ''15 Most Fascinating People of 2010''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.welovesoaps.net/2010/12/15-most-fascinating.html |title=''We Love Soaps'' TV's 15 Most Fascinating People of 2010 |first=Kevin |last=Mulcahy, Jr. |work=[[We Love Soaps]] |date=December 22, 2010 |accessdate=September 30, 2015}}</ref>
In 2017, [[Gothamist]] Washington D.C. affiliate [[DCist]] named ''Anacostia'' "one of the best," in an article highlighting series set in the Washington D.C. area.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dcist.com/2017/03/best_of_dc_web_series.php |title=''DCist'' Ten D.C.-Based Web Series You Should Watch |first=Writer |last=Staff |work=[[DCist]] |date=March 9, 2017 |accessdate=March 11, 2017 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170311213505/http://dcist.com/2017/03/best_of_dc_web_series.php |archivedate=March 11, 2017 |df= }}</ref>
