{{for|the Canadian ice hockey player|Lloyd Klein (ice hockey)}} {{Infobox fashion designer |image = |caption = |name = Lloyd Klein |birth_name = Lloyd David Klein{{r|akiko}} |nationality = |birth_date = |birth_place = [[Montreal|Montréal, Canada]] |death_date = |death_place = |education = |label_name = [[Lloyd Klein Couture]]; LKLA |website = {{url|lloydklein.com}} }}
'''Lloyd David Klein'''<ref name=akiko/> is a French [[couturier]] born in Canada. His fashion label is Lloyd Klein Couture.
==Career== Klein was born in [[Montreal]], Quebec, Canada, to French parents and was raised in [[Paris]], France.<ref name=vesilind>Emili Vesilind (December 6, 2006). [http://www.wwd.com/retail-news/retail-features/lloyd-klein-s-homage-to-elegance-in-l-a-514634?full=true Lloyd Klein’s Homage to Elegance in L.A]. ''Women's Wear Daily. {{subscription required}}</ref> He studied architecture at the [[École Nationale Supérieure des Arts Décoratifs]], and worked in an architect's office in New York.<ref name=akiko/> He returned to Paris<ref name=akiko/> and switched to studying fashion after seeing a [[Givenchy]] runway show;<ref name=moore/> he presented a [[prêt-à-porter]] collection in October 1987.<ref name=akiko/> Klein's first runway show was at the [[Opéra-Comique de Paris]] in 1994.<ref name=moore/> Not long after, he was appointed head designer for the house of [[Grès]]. He then started his own label. In 1998 he moved his business to the United States.<ref name=moore>Booth Moore (January 6, 2007). [http://articles.latimes.com/2007/jan/06/entertainment/et-notebook6 Designs on L.A]. ''Los Angeles Times''. Accessed December 2014.</ref>
[[File:Heinsbergen Decorating Company Building, Los Angeles 3.jpg|thumb]] He opened premises in the [[Heinsbergen Decorating Company Building]] on [[Beverly Boulevard]].<ref>N. Jayne Seward (March 26, 2010). [https://web.archive.org/web/20100612125202/http://www.apparelnews.net/blog/797_a_parisian_afternoon_at_lloyd_klein.html A Parisian Afternoon at Lloyd Klein]. California Apparel News.net. Archived June 21, 2010.{{unreliable source?|date=January 2015}}</ref>
In 2011 Klein appeared as a guest on [[Les Anges de la téléréalité]].<ref>[http://www.melty.fr/les-anges-de-la-tele-realite-saison-3-quotidienne-actu82032.html "Les Anges de la télé-réalité saison 3 : Quotidienne du 19 Octobre"]. melty.fr. 19 October 2011. Accessed January 2015.{{unreliable source?|date=January 2015}}</ref>
In 2012 Klein started marketing sportswear for men and women under the label LKLA.<ref>Erin Weinger (March 2012). [http://www.palmspringslife.com/Palm-Springs-Life/March-2012/A-Look-That-Could-Save-LA-Fashion A Look That Could Save L.A. Fashion] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053640/http://www.palmspringslife.com/Palm-Springs-Life/March-2012/A-Look-That-Could-Save-LA-Fashion/ |date=2013-09-21 }}. ''Palm Springs Life''. Accessed January 2015.</ref> In August 2013 a collaboration between Klein and eyewear manufacturer Ivory Mason was announced.<ref>Danielle Directo-Meston (August 29, 2013). [http://la.racked.com/archives/2013/08/29/las_lloyd_klein_collabs_with_retro_specs_line_ivorymason.php LA's Lloyd Klein Collabs with Retro Specs Line Ivory+Mason]. ''Racked LA''. Accessed January 2015.</ref>
Among those who have worn clothes designed by Klein are: [[Natalie Cole]],<ref>WENN (10 September 2009). [http://www.contactmusic.com/news/cole-returns-to-stage-after-kidney-transplant_1115639 "Cole Returns To Stage After Kidney Transplant"]. contactmusic.com. Accessed January 2015.</ref> [[Paula Abdul]],<ref>[https://archive.is/20110713104003/http://www.paulafan.net/gallery/thumbnails.php?album=395 "paulafan.net"].{{unreliable source?|date=January 2015}}</ref> [[Tara Reid]],<ref>[http://www.peoplestylewatch.com/people/stylewatch/gallery/0,,20042403_9,00.html#20062297 Celeb Fashion Hit or Miss? – Tara Reid]. People.com.</ref> [[Marissa Miller]],<ref>[http://www.alionthego.com/2010/08/09/lloyd-klein/ "Lloyd Klein | Ali On The Go"].</ref> [[Dita von Teese]],<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20140425095953/http://renata-and-jonathan.blogspot.com/2012/12/elegance-above-all-conversation-with.html Elegance Above All | A conversation with Lloyd Klein]. Renata and Jonathan blog. {{unreliable source?|date=January 2015}}</ref> [[Brandy Norwood]] (in "[[It All Belongs To Me]]")<ref>[http://www.realitytvfashion.com/2012/05/monica-brandy-it-all-belongs-to-me-video-fashion "Monica & Brandy “It All Belongs To Me” Video Fashion Round-Up"]. ''Reality TV Fashion & Style | Basketball Wives, Real Housewives of Atlanta, Love & Hip Hop, Being Mary Jane, & More''.{{unreliable source?|date=January 2015}}</ref> and [[Nicki Minaj]] (in "[[Your Love (Nicki Minaj song)|Your Love]]").<ref>[http://style.mtv.com/2010/07/22/nicki-minaj-your-love/ "Look By Look: The Complete Fashion Breakdown Of Nicki Minaj's New Video 'Your Love'"]. ''Style''.</ref>
==Personal life== In February 2004 Klein was badly injured in a car accident outside Paris, and was in [[coma]] for two days. His planned runway show at the [[New York Fashion Week]] was cancelled as a result.<ref>[http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/people/2004-02-10-lloyd-klein_x.htm "USATODAY.com - Designer Lloyd Klein injured in car wreck"].</ref>
