{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2016}} {{Infobox Artwork | image_file=Canaletto - The Entrance to the Grand Canal, Venice - Google Art Project.jpg | alt= | image_size=300px | title=The Entrance to the Grand Canal, Venice | other_language_1= | other_title_1= | artist=[[Canaletto]] | year={{circa|lk=no|1730}} | medium=[[Oil painting|Oil]] on [[canvas]] | height_metric=49.6 | width_metric=73.6 | height_imperial= | width_imperial= | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in }}
'''''The Entrance to the Grand Canal, Venice''''', is an {{circa|lk=no|1730}} [[oil painting]] on [[canvas]] by the [[Republic of Venice|Venetian]] [[Venetian painting|painter]] [[Canaletto]]. It is a [[Rococo]] [[landscape painting]] measuring {{convert|49.6|x|73.6|cm|sp=us}} currently held as part of the Robert Lee Blaffer Memorial Collection in the Audrey Jones Beck Building at the [[Museum of Fine Arts, Houston]], in [[Houston]], Texas. It was a gift from Sarah Campbell Blaffer.<ref name=mfah>[https://www.mfah.org/art/detail/46980 The Entrance to the Grand Canal, Venice, Museum of Fine Arts, Houston]</ref> A variant of the painting with a larger church tower and an additional building is used as the [[Republic of Venice|Venetian]] screen in the 2001 video game ''[[Merchant Prince II]]''.
